Values.Description: the meaning of GLOBAL_COORDS is therefore not to be taken as world coordinate system but as the analysis model specific shared coordinate system
LOCAL_COORDS is to be taken as coordinates which are local to individual structural items and activities

IfcStructuralAnalysisModel.Definition: The IfcStructuralAnalysisModel is used to assemble all information needed to represent a structural analysis model. It encompasses certain general properties (such as analysis type), references to all contained structural members, structural supports or connections, as well as loads and the respective load results.Important functionalities for the description of an analysis model are derived from existing IFC entities: From IfcSystem it inherits the ability to couple the built system via IfcRelReferencedInSpatialStructure to one or more IfcSpatialElement subtypes as necessary.; ; ; From IfcGroup it inherits the inverse attribute IsGroupedBy, pointing to the relationship class IfcRelAssignsToGroup . This allows the grouping of structural members (instances of IfcStructuralMember), and supports (instances of IfcStructuralConnection which belong to a specific analysis model.
IfcStructuralAnalysisModel.Name: Structural Analysis Model

IfcStructuralConnection.Definition: An IfcStructuralConnection represents a structural connection object (node connection, edge connection, or surface connection) or supports.
IfcStructuralConnection.Name: Structural Connection

IfcStructuralCurveAction.Definition: A structural curve action defines an action which is distributed over a curve. A curve action may be connected with a curve member or curve connection, or surface member or surface connection.
IfcStructuralCurveAction.Name: Structural Curve Action

ProjectedOrTrue.Definition: Defines whether load values are given per true length of the curve on which they act, or per length of the projection of the curve in load direction. The latter is only applicable to loads which act in global coordinate directions.

IfcStructuralCurveConnection.Definition: Instances of IfcStructuralCurveConnection describe edge 'nodes', i.e. edges where two or more surface members are joined, or edge supports. Edge curves may be straight or curved.
IfcStructuralCurveConnection.Name: Structural Curve Connection

IfcStructuralCurveMember.Definition: Instances of IfcStructuralCurveMember describe edge members, i.e. structural analysis idealizations of beams, columns, rods etc.. Curve members may be straight or curved.
IfcStructuralCurveMember.Name: Structural Curve Member

IfcStructuralCurveMemberVarying.Definition: This entity describes edge members with varying profile properties. Each instance of IfcStructuralCurveMemberVarying is composed of two or more instances of IfcStructuralCurveMember with differing profile properties. These subordinate members relate to the instance of IfcStructuralCurveMemberVarying by IfcRelAggregates.
IfcStructuralCurveMemberVarying.Name: Structural Curve Member Varying

IfcStructuralCurveReaction.Definition: This entity defines a reaction which occurs distributed over a curve. A curve reaction may be connected with a curve member or curve connection, or surface member or surface connection.
IfcStructuralCurveReaction.Name: Structural Curve Reaction

IfcStructuralItem.Definition: The abstract entity IfcStructuralItem is the generalization of structural members and structural connections, that is, analysis idealizations of elements in the building model. It defines the relation between structural members and connections with structural activities (actions and reactions).Relationships between elements in the building model and structural items as their idealizations can be expressed by instances of IfcRelAssignsToProduct.
IfcStructuralItem.Name: Structural Item

IfcStructuralLinearAction.Definition: This entity defines an action with constant value which is distributed over a curve.
IfcStructuralLinearAction.Name: Structural Linear Action

IfcStructuralLoadCase.Definition: A load case is a load group, commonly used to group loads from the same action source.
IfcStructuralLoadCase.Name: Structural Load Case

SelfWeightCoefficients.Name: Self Weight Coefficients
SelfWeightCoefficients.Definition: The self weight coefficients specify ratios at which loads due to weight of members shall be included in the load case. These loads are not explicitly modeled as instances of IfcStructuralAction. Instead they shall be calculated according to geometry, section, and material of each member.The three components of the self weight vector correspond with the x,y,z directions of the so-called global coordinates, i.e. the directions of the shared ObjectPlacement of all items in an IfcStructuralAnalysisModel. For example, if the object placement defines a z axis which is upright like the IfcProject's world coordinate system, then the self weight coefficients would typically be [0.,0.,-1.] in a load case of dead loads with self weight.The overall coefficient in the inherited attribute Coefficient shall not be applied to SelfWeightCoefficients of the same instance of IfcStructuralLoadCase. It only applies to actions and load groups which are grouped below the load case, not to the load case's computed self weight.

IfcStructuralLoadGroup.Definition: The entity IfcStructuralLoadGroup is used to structure the physical impacts. By using the grouping features inherited from IfcGroup, instances of IfcStructuralAction (or its subclasses) and of IfcStructuralLoadGroup can be used to define load groups, load cases and load combinations. (See also IfcLoadGroupTypeEnum.)
IfcStructuralLoadGroup.Name: Structural Load Group

ActionSource.Definition: Source of actions in the group. Normally needed if 'PredefinedType' specifies a LOAD_CASE.

ActionType.Definition: Type of actions in the group. Normally needed if 'PredefinedType' specifies a LOAD_CASE.

Coefficient.Name: Coefficient
Coefficient.Definition: Load factor. If omitted, a factor is not yet known or not specified. A load factor of 1.0 shall be explicitly exported as Coefficient = 1.0.

Purpose.Name: Purpose
Purpose.Definition: Description of the purpose of this instance. Among else, possible values of the Purpose of load combinations are 'SLS', 'ULS', 'ALS' to indicate serviceability, ultimate, or accidental limit state.

IfcStructuralMember.Definition: The abstract entity IfcStructuralMember is the superclass of all structural items which represent the idealized structural behavior of building elements.
IfcStructuralMember.Name: Structural Member

IfcStructuralPlanarAction.Definition: This entity defines an action with constant value which is distributed over a surface.
IfcStructuralPlanarAction.Name: Structural Planar Action

IfcStructuralPointAction.Definition: This entity defines an action which acts on a point. A point action is typically connected with a point connection. It may also be connected with a curve member or curve connection, or surface member or surface connection.
IfcStructuralPointAction.Name: Structural Point Action

IfcStructuralPointConnection.Definition: Instances of IfcStructuralPointConnection describe structural nodes or point supports.
IfcStructuralPointConnection.Name: Structural Point Connection

IfcStructuralPointReaction.Definition: This entity defines a reaction which occurs at a point. A point reaction is typically connected with a point connection. It may also be connected with a curve member or curve connection, or surface member or surface connection.
IfcStructuralPointReaction.Name: Structural Point Reaction

IfcStructuralReaction.Definition: A structural reaction is a structural activity that results from a structural action imposed to a structural item or building element. Examples are support reactions, internal forces, and deflections.
IfcStructuralReaction.Name: Structural Reaction

IfcStructuralResultGroup.Definition: Instances of the entity IfcStructuralResultGroup are used to group results of structural analysis calculations and to capture the connection to the underlying basic load group. The basic functionality for grouping inherited from IfcGroup is used to collect instances from IfcStructuralReaction or its respective subclasses.
IfcStructuralResultGroup.Name: Structural Result Group

IsLinear.Name: Is Linear
IsLinear.Definition: This value allows to easily recognize whether a linear analysis has been applied (allowing the superposition of analysis results).

TheoryType.Definition: Specifies the analysis theory used to obtain the respective results.

IfcStructuralSurfaceAction.Definition: This entity defines an action which is distributed over a surface. A surface action may be connected with a surface member or surface connection.
IfcStructuralSurfaceAction.Name: Structural Surface Action

ProjectedOrTrue.Definition: Defines whether load values are given per true lengths of the surface on which they act, or per lengths of the projection of the surface in load direction. The latter is only applicable to loads which act in global coordinate directions.

IfcStructuralSurfaceConnection.Definition: Instances of IfcStructuralSurfaceConnection describe face 'nodes', i.e. faces where two or more surface members are joined, or face supports. Face surfaces may be planar or curved.
IfcStructuralSurfaceConnection.Name: Structural Surface Connection

IfcStructuralSurfaceMember.Definition: Instances of IfcStructuralSurfaceMember describe face members, that is, structural analysis idealizations of slabs, walls, and shells. Surface members may be planar or curved.
IfcStructuralSurfaceMember.Name: Structural Surface Member

Thickness.Name: Thickness
Thickness.Definition: Defines the typically understood thickness of the structural surface member, measured normal to its reference surface.

IfcStructuralSurfaceMemberVarying.Definition: This entity describes surface members with varying section properties. The properties are provided by means of Pset_StructuralSurfaceMemberVaryingThickness via IfcRelDefinesByProperties, or by means of aggregation: An instance of IfcStructuralSurfaceMemberVarying may be composed of two or more instances of IfcStructuralSurfaceMember with differing section properties. These subordinate members relate to the instance of IfcStructuralSurfaceMemberVarying by IfcRelAggregates.
IfcStructuralSurfaceMemberVarying.Name: Structural Surface Member Varying

Location1Global.Description: This property in IFC takes list as its value. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
Location1Global.Name: Location1Global
Location1Global.Definition: Global X,Y,Z coordinates of the point in which Thickness1 is given

Location1Local.Description: This property in IFC takes list as its value. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
Location1Local.Name: Location1Local
Location1Local.Definition: Local x,y coordinates of the point in which Thickness1 is given

Location2Global.Description: This property in IFC takes list as its value. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
Location2Global.Name: Location2Global
Location2Global.Definition: Global X,Y,Z coordinates of the point in which Thickness2 is given

Location2Local.Description: This property in IFC takes list as its value. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
Location2Local.Name: Location2Local
Location2Local.Definition: Local x,y coordinates of the point in which Thickness2 is given

Location3Global.Description: This property in IFC takes list as its value. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
Location3Global.Name: Location3Global
Location3Global.Definition: Global X,Y,Z coordinates of the point in which Thickness3 is given

Location3Local.Description: This property in IFC takes list as its value. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
Location3Local.Name: Location3Local
Location3Local.Definition: Local x,y coordinates of the point in which Thickness3 is given

Thickness1.Name: Thickness1
Thickness1.Definition: First thickness parameter of a surface member with varying thickness

Thickness2.Name: Thickness2
Thickness2.Definition: Second thickness parameter of a surface member with varying thickness

Thickness3.Name: Thickness3
Thickness3.Definition: Third thickness parameter of a surface member with varying thickness

IfcStructuralSurfaceReaction.Definition: This entity defines a reaction which occurs distributed over a surface. A surface reaction may be connected with a surface member or surface connection.
IfcStructuralSurfaceReaction.Name: Structural Surface Member Varying Thickness

IfcCaissonFoundation.Definition: CaissonFoundation essentially is a hollow box that can be either open or closed.(
IfcCaissonFoundation.Name: Caisson Foundation

IfcCaissonFoundationType.Definition: Enumeration defining the Caisson Foundation Types.
IfcCaissonFoundationType.Name: Caisson Foundation Type

IfcDeepFoundation.Definition: Deep foundation is a type of foundation that transfers loads deeper than shallow foundation below the soft soils not capable of bearing the above structure. Depending on the soil strength it might have to reach down to the rock layer.Deep foundation is a new supertype incorporating the existing IfcPile and the new IfcCaissonFoundation.
IfcDeepFoundation.Name: Deep Foundation

IfcFooting.Definition: A footing is a part of the foundation of a structure that spreads and transmits the load to the soil. A footing is also characterized as shallow foundation, where the loads are transferred to the ground near the surface.
IfcFooting.Name: Footing

AssemblyPlace.Name: Assembly Place
AssemblyPlace.Definition: Enumeration defining where the assembly is intended to take place, either in a factory, other offsite location or on the building site.

Values.Description: other offsite location or on the building site
other offsite location or on the building site
other offsite location or on the building site

CastingMethod.Name: Casting Method
CastingMethod.Definition: The method of casting the concrete into its designed form.

ConcreteCover.Name: Concrete Cover
ConcreteCover.Definition: The protective concrete cover at the reinforcing bars according to local building regulations.

ConcreteCoverAtLinks.Name: Concrete Cover at Links
ConcreteCoverAtLinks.Definition: The protective concrete cover at the reinforcement links according to local building regulations.

ConcreteCoverAtMainBars.Name: Concrete Cover at Main Bars
ConcreteCoverAtMainBars.Definition: The protective concrete cover at the main reinforcing bars according to local building regulations.

ConstructionToleranceClass.Name: Construction Tolerance Class
ConstructionToleranceClass.Definition: Classification designation of the on-site construction tolerances according to local standards.

DimensionalAccuracyClass.Name: Dimensional Accuracy Class
DimensionalAccuracyClass.Definition: Classification designation of the dimensional accuracy requirement according to local standards.

ExposureClass.Name: Exposure Class
ExposureClass.Definition: Classification of exposure to environmental conditions, usually specified in accordance with the concrete design code which is applied in the project.

ReinforcementAreaRatio.Name: Reinforcement Area Ratio
ReinforcementAreaRatio.Definition: The required ratio of the effective area of the reinforcement to the effective area of the concrete At any section of a reinforced concrete structural element.

ReinforcementStrengthClass.Name: Reinforcement Strength Class
ReinforcementStrengthClass.Definition: Classification of the reinforcement strength in accordance with the concrete design code which is applied in the project. The reinforcing strength class often combines strength and ductility.

ReinforcementVolumeRatio.Name: Reinforcement Volume Ratio
ReinforcementVolumeRatio.Definition: The required ratio of the effective mass of the reinforcement to the effective volume of the concrete of a reinforced concrete structural element.

StrengthClass.Name: Strength Class
StrengthClass.Definition: Classification of the concrete strength in accordance with the concrete design code which is applied in the project.

StructuralClass.Name: Structural Class
StructuralClass.Definition: The structural class defined for the concrete structure (e.g. '1').

LoadBearing.Name: Load Bearing
LoadBearing.Definition: Indicates whether the object is intended to carry loads (TRUE) or not (FALSE).

Values.Description: Indicates whether the object is intended to carry loads (TRUE) or not (FALSE)
Indicates whether the object is intended to carry loads (TRUE) or not (FALSE)

Status.Name: Status
Status.Definition: Status of the element, predominately used in renovation or retrofitting projects. The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition, "Existing" - element exists and remains, "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished, "Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure).

Values.Description: "Demolish" - element existed but is to be demolished
The status can be assigned to as "New" - element designed as new addition
"Temporary" - element will exists only temporary (like a temporary support structure)

AsBuiltLocationNumber.Name: As Built Location Number
AsBuiltLocationNumber.Definition: Defines a unique location within a structure, the slot into which the piece was installed. Where pieces share the same piece mark, they can be interchanged. The value is only known after erection.

PieceMark.Name: Piece Mark
PieceMark.Definition: Defines a unique piece for production purposes. All pieces with the same piece mark value are identical and interchangeable. The piece mark may be composed of sub-parts that have specific locally defined meaning (e.g. B-1A may denote a beam, of generic type 1 and specific shape A).

SerialNumber.Name: Serial Number
SerialNumber.Definition: The manufacturer's serial number assigned to an occurrence of a product.

TypeDesignation.Name: Type Designation
TypeDesignation.Definition: Type designator for the element. The content depends on local standards. Eg. 'Bull nose', 'Half batter', 'Dropper', 'Chamfer' etc

BatterAtEnd.Name: Batter at End
BatterAtEnd.Definition: The angle, in radians, by which the formwork at the ending face of a piece is to be rotated from the vertical in order to compensate for the rotation of the face that will occur once the piece is stripped from its form, inducing camber due to eccentric prestressing.

BatterAtStart.Name: Batter at Start
BatterAtStart.Definition: The angle, in radians, by which the formwork at the starting face of a piece is to be rotated from the vertical in order to compensate for the rotation of the face that will occur once the piece is stripped from its form, inducing camber due to eccentric prestressing.

CamberAtMidspan.Name: Camber at Midspan
CamberAtMidspan.Definition: The camber deflection, measured from the midpoint of a cambered face of a piece to the midpoint of the chord joining the ends of the same face, as shown in the figure below, divided by the original (nominal) straight length of the face of the piece.

CornerChamfer.Name: Corner Chamfer
CornerChamfer.Definition: The chamfer in the corners of the precast element. The chamfer is presumed to be equal in both directions.

DesignLocationNumber.Name: Design Location Number
DesignLocationNumber.Definition: Defines a unique location within a structure, the slot for which the piece was designed.

FormStrippingStrength.Name: Form Stripping Strength
FormStrippingStrength.Definition: The minimum required compressive strength of the concrete at form stripping time.

HollowCorePlugging.Name: Hollow Core Plugging
HollowCorePlugging.Definition: A descriptive label for how the hollow core ends are treated: they may be left open, closed with a plug, or sealed with cast concrete. Values would be, for example: 'Unplugged', 'Plugged', 'SealedWithConcrete'. This property applies to hollow core slabs only.

InitialTension.Name: Initial Tension
InitialTension.Definition: The initial stress of the tendon. This property applies to prestressed concrete elements only.

LiftingStrength.Name: Lifting Strength
LiftingStrength.Definition: The minimum required compressive strength of the concrete when the concrete element is lifted.

ManufacturingToleranceClass.Name: Manufacturing Tolerance Class
ManufacturingToleranceClass.Definition: Classification designation of the manufacturing tolerances according to local standards.

PieceMark.Name: Piece Mark
PieceMark.Definition: Defines a unique piece for production purposes. All pieces with the same piece mark value are identical and interchangeable. The piece mark may be composed of sub-parts that have specific locally defined meaning (e.g. B-1A may denote a beam, of generic type 1 and specific shape A).

ReleaseStrength.Name: Release Strength
ReleaseStrength.Definition: The minimum required compressive strength of the concrete when the tendon stress is released. This property applies to prestressed concrete elements only.

Shortening.Name: Shortening
Shortening.Definition: The ratio of the distance by which a precast piece is shortened after release from its form (due to compression induced by prestressing) to its original (nominal) length.

SupportDuringTransportDescription.Name: Support During Transport Description
SupportDuringTransportDescription.Definition: Textual description of how the concrete element is supported during transportation.

SupportDuringTransportDocReference.Description: This property in IFC takes as its value a reference to one of: IfcAddress, IfcAppliedValue, IfcExternalReference, IfcMaterialDefinition, IfcOrganization, IfcPerson, IfcPersonAndOrganization, IfcTable, IfcTimeSeries. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
SupportDuringTransportDocReference.Name: Support During Transport Doc Reference
SupportDuringTransportDocReference.Definition: Reference to an external document defining how the concrete element is supported during transportation.

TendonRelaxation.Name: Tendon Relaxation
TendonRelaxation.Definition: The maximum allowable relaxation of the tendon (usually expressed as %/1000 h).This property applies to prestressed concrete elements only.

TransportationStrength.Name: Transportation Strength
TransportationStrength.Definition: The minimum required compressive strength of the concrete required for transportation.

Twisting.Name: Twisting
Twisting.Definition: The angle, in radians, through which the end face of a precast piece is rotated with respect to its starting face, along its longitudinal axis, as a result of non-aligned supports. This measure is also termed the warping angle.

TypeDesignation.Name: Type Designation
TypeDesignation.Definition: Type designator for the element. The content depends on local standards. Eg. 'Bull nose', 'Half batter', 'Dropper', 'Chamfer' etc

XDirectionLowerBarCount.Name: Xdirection Lower Bar Count
XDirectionLowerBarCount.Definition: The number of bars with X direction lower bar.

XDirectionUpperBarCount.Name: Xdirection Upper Bar Count
XDirectionUpperBarCount.Definition: The number of bars with X direction upper bar.

YDirectionLowerBarCount.Name: Ydirection Lower Bar Count
YDirectionLowerBarCount.Definition: The number of bars with Y direction lower bar.

YDirectionUpperBarCount.Name: Ydirection Upper Bar Count
YDirectionUpperBarCount.Definition: The number of bars with Y direction upper bar.

CrossingLowerBarPitch.Name: Crossing Lower Bar Pitch
CrossingLowerBarPitch.Definition: The pitch length of the crossing lower bar.

CrossingUpperBarPitch.Name: Crossing Upper Bar Pitch
CrossingUpperBarPitch.Definition: The pitch length of the crossing upper bar.

CrossSectionArea.Name: Cross Section Area
CrossSectionArea.Definition: Total area of the cross section (or profile) of the object.

GrossSurfaceArea.Name: Gross Surface Area
GrossSurfaceArea.Definition: Total gross area of the object, normally generated as perimeter * length + 2 * cross section area. It is the sum of OuterSurfaceArea + (2 x CrossSectionArea) and shall only be given, if the OuterSurfaceArea and CrossSectionArea cannot be established separately.

GrossVolume.Name: Gross Volume
GrossVolume.Definition: Total gross volume of the object. Openings, recesses, enclosed objects and projections are not taken into account.

GrossWeight.Name: Gross Weight
GrossWeight.Definition: Total Gross Weight of the object without any add-on parts and not taking into account possible processing features (cut-out's, etc.) or openings and recesses.

NetVolume.Name: Net Volume
NetVolume.Definition: Total net volume of the object, taking into account possible processing features (cut-out's, etc.) or openings and recesses.

NetWeight.Name: Net Weight
NetWeight.Definition: Total net weight of the object without add-on parts, taking into account possible processing features (cut-out's, etc.) or openings and recesses.

OuterSurfaceArea.Name: Outer Surface Area
OuterSurfaceArea.Definition: Total area of the surfaces of the object (not taking into account the end cap areas), normally generated as perimeter * length in case of extrusions.

Width.Name: Width
Width.Definition: The width of the object. Only given, if the object has constant thickness (prismatic).

IfcFootingType.Definition: The building element type IfcFootingType defines commonly shared information for occurrences of footings. The set of shared information may include: common properties with shared property sets; common representations; common materials; common composition of elementsIt is used to define a footing type specification indicating the specific product information that is common to all occurrences of that product type. The IfcFootingType may be declared within IfcProject or IfcProjectLibrary using IfcRelDeclares and may be exchanged with or without occurrences of the type. Occurrences of IfcFootingType are represented by instances of IfcFooting. Refer to the documentation at IfcFooting for supported property sets, materials, and composition.
IfcFootingType.Name: Footing Type

IfcPile.Definition: A pile is a slender timber, concrete, or steel structural element, driven, jetted, or otherwise embedded on end in the ground for the purpose of supporting a load. A pile is also characterized as deep foundation, where the loads are transferred to deeper subsurface layers.
IfcPile.Name: Pile

IfcPileType.Definition: The building element type IfcPileType defines commonly shared information for occurrences of piles. The set of shared information may include: common properties with shared property sets; common representations; common materials; common composition of elementsIt is used to define a pile type specification indicating the specific product information that is common to all occurrences of that product type. The IfcPileType may be declared within IfcProject or IfcProjectLibrary using IfcRelDeclares and may be exchanged with or without occurrences of the type. Occurrences of IfcPileType are represented by instances of IfcPile. Refer to the documentation at IfcPile for supported property sets, materials, and composition.
IfcPileType.Name: Pile Type

IfcReinforcementDefinitionProperties.Definition: IfcReinforcementDefinitionProperties defines the cross section properties of reinforcement included in reinforced concrete building elements. The property set definition may be used both in conjunction with insitu and precast structures.This subtype of IfcPropertySetDefinition is used to define the reinforcement properties in early design stages, such as in requirement definition or scheme design. In later design stages explicit instances of subtypes of IfcReinforcingElement are used. The intended usage may be indicated using the DefinitionType attribute value as a designator: recommended values are 'Reinforcement area requirement' or 'Reinforcement configuration requirement'. Other values may be used according to local standards.Only one property set definition of this kind is used for each concrete building element in each intended usage indicated by the DefinitionType attribute value. This set then defines a list of cross section properties in a discrete number of longitudinal sections as instances of IfcSectionReinforcementProperties (one for each structural reinforcement bar role), which in turn have a section cross section property defined as a profile and a number of reinforcement properties, one for each steel grade / bar type.
IfcReinforcementDefinitionProperties.Name: Reinforcement Definition Properties

DefinitionType.Name: Definition Type
DefinitionType.Definition: Descriptive type name applied to reinforcement definition properties.

IfcReinforcingBar.Definition: A reinforcing bar is usually made of steel with manufactured deformations in the surface, and used in concrete and masonry construction to provide additional strength. A single instance of this class may represent one or many of actual rebars, for example a row of rebars.
IfcReinforcingBar.Name: Reinforcing Bar

BarLength.Name: Bar Length
BarLength.Definition: The total length of the reinforcing bar. The total length of bended bars are calculated according to local standards with corrections for the bends.

BarSurface.Definition: Indicator for whether the bar surface is plain or textured.

Values.Description: Indicator for whether the bar surface is plain or textured
Indicator for whether the bar surface is plain or textured

CrossSectionArea.Name: Cross Section Area
CrossSectionArea.Definition: The effective cross-section area of the reinforcing bar.

NominalDiameter.Name: Nominal Diameter
NominalDiameter.Definition: The nominal diameter defining the cross-section size of the reinforcing bar.

BendingShapeCode.Name: Bending Shape Code
BendingShapeCode.Definition: Shape code per a standard like ACI 315, ISO 3766, or a similar standard. It is presumed that a single standard for defining the bar bending is used throughout the project and that this standard is referenced from the IfcProject object through the IfcDocumentReference mechanism.

IfcReinforcingBarType.Definition: The reinforcing element type IfcReinforcingBarType defines commonly shared information for occurrences of reinforcing bars. The set of shared information may include: common properties with shared property sets; common representations; common materials; common composition of elementsIt is used to define a reinforcing bar type specification indicating the specific product information that is common to all occurrences of that product type. The IfcReinforcingBarType may be declared within IfcProject or IfcProjectLibrary using IfcRelDeclares and may be exchanged with or without occurrences of the type. Occurrences of IfcReinforcingBarType are represented by instances of IfcReinforcingBar.
IfcReinforcingBarType.Name: Reinforcing Bar Type

IfcReinforcingElement.Definition: A reinforcing element represents bars, wires, strands, meshes, tendons, and other components embedded in concrete in such a manner that the reinforcement and the concrete act together in resisting forces.
IfcReinforcingElement.Name: Reinforcing Element

IfcReinforcingElementType.Definition: The element component type IfcReinforcingElementType defines commonly shared information for occurrences of reinforcing elements. The set of shared information may include: common properties with shared property sets; common representations; common materials; common composition of elementsIt is used to define a reinforcing element type specification indicating the specific product information that is common to all occurrences of that product type. The IfcReinforcingElementType may be declared within IfcProject or IfcProjectLibrary using IfcRelDeclares and may be exchanged with or without occurrences of the type. Occurrences of IfcReinforcingElementType are represented by instances of IfcReinforcingElement.
IfcReinforcingElementType.Name: Reinforcing Element Type

IfcReinforcingMesh.Definition: A reinforcing mesh is a series of longitudinal and transverse wires or bars of various gauges, arranged at right angles to each other and welded at all points of intersection; usually used for concrete slab reinforcement. It is also known as welded wire fabric. In scope are plane meshes as well as bent meshes.
IfcReinforcingMesh.Name: Reinforcing Mesh

LongitudinalBarCrossSectionArea.Name: Longitudinal Bar Cross Section Area
LongitudinalBarCrossSectionArea.Definition: The effective cross-section area of the longitudinal bars of the mesh.

LongitudinalBarNominalDiameter.Name: Longitudinal Bar Nominal Diameter
LongitudinalBarNominalDiameter.Definition: The nominal diameter denoting the cross-section size of the longitudinal bars.

LongitudinalBarSpacing.Name: Longitudinal Bar Spacing
LongitudinalBarSpacing.Definition: The spacing between the longitudinal bars. Note: an even distribution of bars is presumed; other cases are handled by classification or property sets.

MeshLength.Name: Mesh Length
MeshLength.Definition: The overall length of the mesh measured in its longitudinal direction.

MeshWidth.Name: Mesh Width
MeshWidth.Definition: The overall width of the mesh measured in its transversal direction.

TransverseBarCrossSectionArea.Name: Transverse Bar Cross Section Area
TransverseBarCrossSectionArea.Definition: The effective cross-section area of the transverse bars of the mesh.

TransverseBarNominalDiameter.Name: Transverse Bar Nominal Diameter
TransverseBarNominalDiameter.Definition: The nominal diameter denoting the cross-section size of the transverse bars.

TransverseBarSpacing.Name: Transverse Bar Spacing
TransverseBarSpacing.Definition: The spacing between the transverse bars. Note: an even distribution of bars is presumed; other cases are handled by classification or property sets.

BendingShapeCode.Name: Bending Shape Code
BendingShapeCode.Definition: If this mesh type is bent rather than planar, this attribute provides a shape code per a standard like ACI 315, ISO 3766, or a similar standard. It is presumed that a single standard for defining the mesh bending is used throughout the project and that this standard is referenced from the IfcProject object through the IfcDocumentReference mechanism.

IfcReinforcingMeshType.Definition: The reinforcing element type IfcReinforcingMeshType defines commonly shared information for occurrences of reinforcing meshs. The set of shared information may include: common properties with shared property sets; common representations; common materials; common composition of elementsIt is used to define a reinforcing mesh type specification indicating the specific product information that is common to all occurrences of that product type. The IfcReinforcingMeshType may be declared within IfcProject or IfcProjectLibrary using IfcRelDeclares and may be exchanged with or without occurrences of the type. Occurrences of IfcReinforcingMeshType are represented by instances of IfcReinforcingMesh.
IfcReinforcingMeshType.Name: Reinforcing Mesh Type

IfcSurfaceFeature.Definition: A surface feature is a modification at (onto, or into) of the surface of an element. Parts of the surface of the entire surface may be affected. The volume and mass of the element may be increased, remain unchanged, or be decreased by the surface feature, depending on manufacturing technology. However, any increase or decrease of volume is small compared to the total volume of the element.The partwhole relationship is established by an aggregation relationship object, expressing the decomposition of an element type into one or more additive elements (element parts) and zero or more feature elements.
IfcSurfaceFeature.Name: Surface Feature

IfcTendon.Definition: A tendon is a steel element such as a wire, cable, bar, rod, or strand used to impart prestress to concrete when the element is tensioned.
IfcTendon.Name: Tendon

AnchorageSlip.Name: Anchorage Slip
AnchorageSlip.Definition: The deformation of an anchor or slippage of tendons when the prestressing device is released.

CrossSectionArea.Name: Cross Section Area
CrossSectionArea.Definition: The effective cross-section area of the prestressed part of the tendon.

FrictionCoefficient.Name: Friction Coefficient
FrictionCoefficient.Definition: The friction coefficient between tendon and tendon sheet while the tendon is unbonded.

MinCurvatureRadius.Name: Min Curvature Radius
MinCurvatureRadius.Definition: The smallest curvature radius calculated on the whole effective length of the tendon where the tension properties are still valid.

NominalDiameter.Name: Nominal Diameter
NominalDiameter.Definition: The nominal diameter defining the cross-section size of the prestressed part of the tendon.

PreStress.Name: Pre Stress
PreStress.Definition: The prestress to be applied on the tendon.

TensionForce.Name: Tension Force
TensionForce.Definition: The maximum allowed tension force that can be applied on the tendon.

SheathDiameter.Name: Sheath Diameter
SheathDiameter.Definition: Diameter of the sheeth (duct) around the tendon, if there is one with this type of tendon.

IfcTendonAnchor.Definition: A tendon anchor is the end connection for tendons in prestressed or posttensioned concrete.
IfcTendonAnchor.Name: Tendon Anchor

IfcTendonAnchorType.Definition: The reinforcing element type IfcTendonAnchorType defines commonly shared information for occurrences of tendon anchors. The set of shared information may include: common properties with shared property sets; common representations; common materials; common composition of elementsIt is used to define a tendon anchor type specification indicating the specific product information that is common to all occurrences of that product type. The IfcTendonAnchorType may be declared within IfcProject or IfcProjectLibrary using IfcRelDeclares and may be exchanged with or without occurrences of the type. Occurrences of IfcTendonAnchorType are represented by instances of IfcTendonAnchor.
IfcTendonAnchorType.Name: Tendon Anchor Type

IfcTendonConduit.Definition: A TendonConduit represents the components of the conduit system for tendons embedded in concrete structure.
IfcTendonConduit.Name: Tendon Conduit

IfcTendonType.Definition: The reinforcing element type IfcTendonType defines commonly shared information for occurrences of tendons. The set of shared information may include: common properties with shared property sets; common representations; common materials; common composition of elementsIt is used to define a tendon type specification indicating the specific product information that is common to all occurrences of that product type. The IfcTendonType may be declared within IfcProject or IfcProjectLibrary using IfcRelDeclares and may be exchanged with or without occurrences of the type. Occurrences of IfcTendonType are represented by instances of IfcTendon.
IfcTendonType.Name: Tendon Type

IfcVoidingFeature.Definition: A voiding feature is a modification of an element which reduces its volume. Such a feature may be manufactured in different ways, for example by cutting, drilling, or milling of members made of various materials, or by inlays into the formwork of cast members made of materials such as concrete.The standard use of instances of IfcVoidingFeature is as a part of element type objects (instances of subtypes of IfcElementType). The partwhole relationship is established by an aggregation relationship object, expressing the decomposition of an element type into one or more additive elements (element parts) and zero or more feature elements.
IfcVoidingFeature.Name: Qto_Reinforcing Element Base Quantities

IfcCableCarrierFitting.BEND.Definition: A fitting that changes the route of the cable carrier.
IfcCableCarrierFitting.BEND.Name: Bend

BendAngle.Definition: The change of direction of flow.

BendRadius.Definition: The radius of bending if circular arc or zero if sharp bend.

IfcCableCarrierFitting.CONNECTOR.Name: Connector

IfcCableCarrierFitting.CROSS.Definition: A fitting at which two branches are taken from the main route of the cable carrier simultaneously.
IfcCableCarrierFitting.CROSS.Name: Cross

IfcCableCarrierFitting.JUNCTION.Definition: A fitting with typically more than two ports used to redistribute flow among the ports and/or to change the direction of flow between connected elements (e.g, tee, cross, wye, etc.).
IfcCableCarrierFitting.JUNCTION.Name: Junction

JunctionRightAngle.Name: Junction Right Angle
JunctionRightAngle.Definition: The change of direction of flow for the right junction where 0 indicates straight segment.

JunctionRightRadius.Name: Junction Right Radius
JunctionRightRadius.Definition: The radius of bending for the right junction where 0 indicates sharp bend.

JunctionType.Name: Junction Type
JunctionType.Definition: The type of junction. TEE=3 ports, CROSS = 4 ports.

IfcCableCarrierFitting.REDUCER.Definition: A fitting that changes the physical size of the main route of the cable carrier.
IfcCableCarrierFitting.REDUCER.Name: Reducer

IfcCableCarrierFitting.TEE.Definition: A fitting at which a branch is taken from the main route of the cable carrier.
IfcCableCarrierFitting.TEE.Name: Tee

IfcCableCarrierFitting.TRANSITION.Definition: A fitting with typically two ports having different shapes or sizes. Can also be used to change the direction of flow between connected elements.
IfcCableCarrierFitting.TRANSITION.Name: Transition

Construction.Name: Construction
Construction.Definition: Purpose of informing on how the vonductor is constructed (interwined or solid). I.e. Solid (IEV 461-01-06), stranded (IEV 461-01-07), solid-/finestranded(IEV 461-01-11) (not flexible/flexible).

Function.Name: Function

OverallDiameter.Name: Overall Diameter

RatedVoltage.Definition: The range of allowed voltage that a device is certified to handle. The upper bound of this value is the maximum.

ThermalExpansionCoefficient.Name: Thermal Expansion Coefficient
ThermalExpansionCoefficient.Definition: Quantity characterizing the variation with thermodynamic temperature T of the distance l between two points of a body, under given conditions (IEC 113-04-27). The ratio is defined per Kelvin.

UltimateTensileStrength.Name: Ultimate Tensile Strength
UltimateTensileStrength.Definition: Indicates the maximum stress that a material or element can withstand before breaking while being stretched or pulled.

YoungModulus.Name: Young Modulus
YoungModulus.Definition: A measure of the Young's modulus of elasticity of the material.

ResistanceToGround.Name: Resistance to Ground
ResistanceToGround.Definition: The resistance through earthing conductor to the ground. Real part of the impedance to earth [SOURCE IEC: 195-01-18]

IfcCableSegment.CORESEGMENT.Definition: A self contained element of a cable that comprises one or more conductors and sheathing.The core of one lead is normally single wired or multiwired which are intertwined.
IfcCableSegment.CORESEGMENT.Name: Core Segment

CoreIdentifier.Name: Core Identifier
CoreIdentifier.Definition: The core identification used Identifiers may be used such as by color (Black, Brown, Grey) or by number (1, 2, 3) or by IEC phase reference (L1, L2, L3) etc.

FunctionReliable.Name: Function Reliable
FunctionReliable.Definition: Element (such as cable, bus, core) maintain given properties/functions over a given (tested) time and conditions. According to IEC standard.

HalogenProof.Name: Halogen Proof
HalogenProof.Definition: Produces small amount of smoke and irritating Deaerator/Gas.

LayRatio.Name: Lay Ratio
LayRatio.Definition: The ratio between lay length and the diameter of the single conductor.

ScreenDiameter.Definition: The diameter of the screen around an object (if present).

SelfExtinguishing60332_1.Name: Self Extinguishing60332_1
SelfExtinguishing60332_1.Definition: Self Extinguishing cable/core according to IEC 60332.1.

SelfExtinguishing60332_3.Name: Self Extinguishing60332_3
SelfExtinguishing60332_3.Definition: Self Extinguishing cable/core according to IEC 60332.3.

SheathColours.Name: Sheath Colours
SheathColours.Definition: Colour of the core (derived from IEC 60757). Note that the combined color 'GreenAndYellow' shall be used only as Protective Earth (PE) conductors according to the requirements of IEC 60446.

Standard.Name: Standard
Standard.Definition: The designation of the standard applicable for the definition of the object used.

StrandingMethod.Name: Stranding Method
StrandingMethod.Definition: Specifies the method used to strand the cable. Stranding is the process where a particular number of stranding elements are joined together while winding them round a common axis.

TensileStrength.Name: Tensile Strength

IfcCableSegment.FIBERSEGMENT.Definition: A fiber segment is an individual optical fiber used in telecommunication systems to transmit data by means of optical signals.
IfcCableSegment.FIBERSEGMENT.Name: Fiber Segment

InUse.Name: In Use
InUse.Definition: Indicates whether the fiber has been assigned to some specific use.

FiberColour.Name: Fiber Colour
FiberColour.Definition: Indicates the colour of a single fiber.

FiberType.Name: Fiber Type
FiberType.Definition: Indicates the type of the single fiber.

HasTightJacket.Name: Has Tight Jacket
HasTightJacket.Definition: Indicates whether the fiber has a tight jacket or not.

IfcCableSegment.FIBERTUBE.Definition: A fiber tube is semi-rigid hollow plastic tube with a very small radius that houses and protects a certain number of optical fiber segments. An optical cable segment may contain many fiber tubes.
IfcCableSegment.FIBERTUBE.Name: Fiber Tube

FiberTubeColour.Name: Fiber Tube Colour
FiberTubeColour.Definition: Indicates the colour of a single fiber tube.

NumberOfFibers.Name: Number of Fibers
NumberOfFibers.Definition: Indicates the number of fibers in the single tube or cable.

IfcCableSegment.OPTICALCABLESEGMENT.Definition: An optical cable segment is a cable segment that contains a variable number of optical fiber segments.
IfcCableSegment.OPTICALCABLESEGMENT.Name: Optical Cable Segment

NumberOfFibers.Name: Number of Fibers
NumberOfFibers.Definition: Indicates the number of fibers in the single tube or cable.

NumberOfMultiModeFibers.Name: Number of Multi Mode Fibers
NumberOfMultiModeFibers.Definition: Total number of multi-mode fibers in the optical fiber cable.

NumberOfSingleModeFibers.Name: Number of Single Mode Fibers
NumberOfSingleModeFibers.Definition: Total number of single-mode fibers in the optical fiber cable.

OpticalCableStructure.Name: Optical Cable Structure
OpticalCableStructure.Definition: Distinguishes between different structures of an optical fiber cable.

FiberType.Name: Fiber Type
FiberType.Definition: Indicates the type of the single fiber.

JacketColour.Name: Jacket Colour
JacketColour.Definition: Indicates the colour of the cable or fitting jacket.

JacketColour.Name: Jacket Colour
JacketColour.Definition: Indicates the colour of the cable or fitting jacket.

IfcCableSegment.STITCHWIRE.Definition: A stitch wire consists of auxiliary wires and different components (clamp) used in stitched suspension.
IfcCableSegment.STITCHWIRE.Name: Stitchwire

AssemblyInstruction.Description: This property in IFC takes as its value a reference to one of: IfcAddress, IfcAppliedValue, IfcExternalReference, IfcMaterialDefinition, IfcOrganization, IfcPerson, IfcPersonAndOrganization, IfcTable, IfcTimeSeries. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
AssemblyInstruction.Name: Assembly Instruction
AssemblyInstruction.Definition: Instructions to describe how the system / equipment / facility is assembled.

MechanicalTension.Name: Mechanical Tension
MechanicalTension.Definition: Nominal value of mechanical force applied to a flow segment.

NominalLength.Name: Nominal Length
NominalLength.Definition: The nominal overall length of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

TensileStrength.Name: Tensile Strength
TensileStrength.Definition: Indicates the ability to withstand breakage apart under applied force.

UltimateTensileStrength.Name: Ultimate Tensile Strength
UltimateTensileStrength.Definition: Indicates the maximum stress that a material or element can withstand before breaking while being stretched or pulled.

IfcCableSegment.WIREPAIRSEGMENT.Definition: A pair of conductors contained in a copper cable. The pair is always used together to form a circuit to transmit data by means of electric signals.
IfcCableSegment.WIREPAIRSEGMENT.Name: Wi Repair Segment

CharacteristicImpedance.Name: Characteristic Impedance
CharacteristicImpedance.Definition: A quantity defined for a mode of propagation at a given frequency in a specific uniform transmission line or uniform waveguide by one of the three following relations: ; Z1 = S/ |I|2; Z2 = |U|2 / S; Z3 = U / I; where Z is the complex characteristic impedance, S the complex power and U and I are the values, usually complex, respectively of a voltage and a current conventionally defined for each type of mode by analogy with transmission line equations.

ConductorDiameter.Name: Conductor Diameter
ConductorDiameter.Definition: Indicates the conductor diameter. It is only used for twisted and untwisted wire pair.

CoreConductorDiameter.Name: Core Conductor Diameter
CoreConductorDiameter.Definition: Indicates the core conductor diameter. It is only used for coaxial wire pair.

JacketColour.Name: Jacket Colour
JacketColour.Definition: Indicates the colour of the cable or fitting jacket.

ShieldConductorDiameter.Name: Shield Conductor Diameter
ShieldConductorDiameter.Definition: Indicates the shielded conductor diameter. It is only used for coaxial wire pair.

WirePairType.Name: Wire Pair Type
WirePairType.Definition: Indicates the type of wire pair, i.e., twisted, untwisted or coaxial pair.

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.ANTENNA.Definition: A transducer designed to transmit or receive electromagnetic waves.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.ANTENNA.Name: Antenna

AntennaGain.Name: Antenna Gain
AntennaGain.Definition: Indicates the antenna gain, which is a ratio of the power transmitted by an antenna in a specific direction compared to an isotropic antenna.

PolarizationMode.Name: Polarization Mode
PolarizationMode.Definition: Indicates the polarization mode of antenna.

RadiationPattern.Name: Radiation Pattern
RadiationPattern.Definition: Indicates the radiation pattern of antenna.

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.AUTOMATON.Definition: A self-acting artificial device, the behaviour of which is governed either in a stepwise manner by given decision rules or continuously in time by defined relationships, while the output variables of which are created from its input and state variables.; Note: definition from IEC 60050-351-42-32.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.AUTOMATON.Name: Auto Maton

InputSignalType.Name: Input Signal Type
InputSignalType.Definition: The type of the input signal.

OutputSignalType.Name: Output Signal Type
OutputSignalType.Definition: The type of the output signal.

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.COMPUTER.Definition: A desktop, laptop, tablet, or other type of computer that can be moved from one place to another and connected to an electrical supply via a plugged outlet.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.COMPUTER.Name: Computer

StorageCapacity.Name: Storage Capacity
StorageCapacity.Definition: Indicates the total data storage capacity of the device. It is defined by bytes.

UserInterfaceType.Name: User Interface Type
UserInterfaceType.Definition: Indicates the user interface of the computer.

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.FAX.Definition: A machine that has the primary function of transmitting a facsimile copy of printed matter using a telephone line.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.FAX.Name: Fax

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.GATEWAY.Definition: A gateway connects multiple network segments with different protocols at all layers (layers 1-7) of the Open Systems Interconnection (OSI) model.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.GATEWAY.Name: Gate Way

NumberOfInterfaces.Description: This property in IFC takes a table as its value. That table has two columns (two lists), one for defining and other for defined values. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
NumberOfInterfaces.Name: Number of Interfaces
NumberOfInterfaces.Definition: Indicates the types of interfaces and their number in the device.

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.INTELLIGENTPE.Definition: An intelligent peripheral is a device that offers a variety of specialized resources according to the corresponding service logical program under the control of SCP. These resources contain the receiver of DTMF (Dual-Tone Multi-Frequency, signal generator, record notice, etc.). An intelligent peripheral provides dedicated resource functions in the intelligent network, allocates, controls and manages various dedicated resources, communicates with other entities in the network, and completes SRF resource functions as well as the maintenance, management and statistics functions of resources.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.INTELLIGENTPE.Name: Intelligent Peripheral

UserCapacity.Name: User Capacity
UserCapacity.Definition: Indicates the user capacity of the device, defined as the maximum number of users that can be active at the same time.

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.IPNETWORKEQUI.Definition: An IP network equipment is a device that provides IP data transmission channel for telecom subsystems or other subsystems e.g., routers, network switches or firewalls.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.IPNETWORKEQUI.Name: Ip Network Equipment

EquipmentCapacity.Name: Equipment Capacity
EquipmentCapacity.Definition: Indicates the equipment capacity of the appliance. The value is defined in bits/s.

ManagingSoftware.Name: Managing Software
ManagingSoftware.Definition: Indicates the type of software responsible for managing the equipment.

NumberOfCoolingFans.Name: Number of Cooling Fans
NumberOfCoolingFans.Definition: Indicates the number of cooling fans in the equipment.

NumberOfInterfaces.Description: This property in IFC takes a table as its value. That table has two columns (two lists), one for defining and other for defined values. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
NumberOfInterfaces.Name: Number of Interfaces
NumberOfInterfaces.Definition: Indicates the types of interfaces and their number in the device.

SupportedProtocol.Name: Supported Protocol
SupportedProtocol.Definition: Indicates the protocol supported by the IP network equipment.

NumberOfPackets.Description: This property in IFC takes as its value a reference to one of: IfcAddress, IfcAppliedValue, IfcExternalReference, IfcMaterialDefinition, IfcOrganization, IfcPerson, IfcPersonAndOrganization, IfcTable, IfcTimeSeries. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
NumberOfPackets.Name: Number of Packets
NumberOfPackets.Definition: Indicates the number of packets of the IP network equipment.

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.LINESIDEELECT.Definition: The lineside electronic unit (LEU) is the interface between the balise and interlocking in railway. The LEU acquires the information from the interlocking, and sends the appropriate information to the balises in concordance with the lineside signalling (if available).
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.LINESIDEELECT.Name: Line Side Electronic Unit

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.MODEM.Definition: A modem (from modulator-demodulator) is a device that modulates an analog carrier signal to encode digital information, and also demodulates such a carrier signal to decode the transmitted information.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.MODEM.Name: Modem

CommonInterfaceType.Name: Common Interface Type
CommonInterfaceType.Definition: Indicates the type of the device common interfaces.

NumberOfCommonInterfaces.Description: This property in IFC takes a table as its value. That table has two columns (two lists), one for defining and other for defined values. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
NumberOfCommonInterfaces.Name: Number of Common Interfaces
NumberOfCommonInterfaces.Definition: Indicates the number of common interfaces on the device.

NumberOfTrafficInterfaces.Description: This property in IFC takes a table as its value. That table has two columns (two lists), one for defining and other for defined values. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
NumberOfTrafficInterfaces.Name: Number of Traffic Interfaces
NumberOfTrafficInterfaces.Definition: Indicates the number of traffic interfaces on the device.

TrafficInterfaceType.Name: Traffic Interface Type
TrafficInterfaceType.Definition: Indicates the type of the device traffic interfaces.

DataTransmissionUnitUsage.Name: Data Transmission Unit Usage
DataTransmissionUnitUsage.Definition: Indicates the usage of the data transmission unit. It can be used to transmit data for different types of sensors.

SerialInterfaceType.Name: Serial Interface Type
SerialInterfaceType.Definition: Indicates the type of serial interface used by the device.

WorkingState.Name: Working State
WorkingState.Definition: Indicates the working state of device or system.

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.NETWORKAPPLIA.Definition: A network appliance performs a dedicated function such as firewall protection, content filtering, load balancing, or equipment management.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.NETWORKAPPLIA.Name: Network Appliance

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.NETWORKBRIDGE.Definition: A network bridge connects multiple network segments at the data link layer (layer 2) of the OSI model, and the term layer 2 switch is very often used interchangeably with bridge.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.NETWORKBRIDGE.Name: Network Bridge

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.NETWORKHUB.Definition: A network hub connects multiple network segments at the physical layer (layer 1) of the OSI model.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.NETWORKHUB.Name: Network Hub

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.OPTICALLINETE.Definition: An optical line terminal is a service provider endpoint of a passive or active optical network. It is the terminal equipment for connecting fiber optic trunks.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.OPTICALLINETE.Name: Opticalline Terminal

NumberOfInterfaces.Description: This property in IFC takes a table as its value. That table has two columns (two lists), one for defining and other for defined values. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
NumberOfInterfaces.Name: Number of Interfaces
NumberOfInterfaces.Definition: Indicates the types of interfaces and their number in the device.

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.OPTICALNETWOR.Definition: An optical network unit is a kind of optical transmission network connection equipment which is installed at user side.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.OPTICALNETWOR.Name: Optical Network Unit

NumberOfInterfaces.Description: This property in IFC takes a table as its value. That table has two columns (two lists), one for defining and other for defined values. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
NumberOfInterfaces.Name: Number of Interfaces
NumberOfInterfaces.Definition: Indicates the types of interfaces and their number in the device.

OpticalNetworkUnitType.Name: Optical Network Unit Type
OpticalNetworkUnitType.Definition: Indicates the type of the optical network unit equipment.

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.PRINTER.Definition: A machine that has the primary function of printing text and/or graphics onto paper or other media.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.PRINTER.Name: Printer

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.RADIOBLOCKCEN.Definition: A radio block center is a specialised computing device in railway with specification for generating Movement Authorities (MA) and transmitting it to trains. It gets information from signalling control and from the trains in its section.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.RADIOBLOCKCEN.Name: Radioblock Center

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.REPEATER.Definition: A repeater is an electronic device that receives a signal and retransmits it at a higher level and/or higher power, or onto the other side of an obstruction, so that the signal can cover longer distances without degradation.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.REPEATER.Name: Repeater

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.ROUTER.Definition: A router is a networking device whose software and hardware are usually tailored to the tasks of routing and forwarding information. For example, on the Internet, information is directed to various paths by routers.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.ROUTER.Name: Router

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.SCANNER.Definition: A machine that has the primary function of scanning the content of printed matter and converting it to digital format that can be stored in a computer.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.SCANNER.Name: Scanner

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.TELECOMMAND.Definition: A system sending command to control and monitor the switches and circuit breakers or systems directly or not connected (e.g. via wires) within the traction power system remotely.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.TELECOMMAND.Name: Telecommand

NumberOfCPUs.Name: Number of Cpus
NumberOfCPUs.Definition: The number of CPUs used by the equipment.

NumberOfWorkstations.Description: This property in IFC takes a table as its value. That table has two columns (two lists), one for defining and other for defined values. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
NumberOfWorkstations.Name: Number of Workstations
NumberOfWorkstations.Definition: Indicates the types or purposes of workstations and their number in the equipment. The defined purpose can be e.g. 'Diagnostic and maintenance', 'Traffic and electric traction', etc.

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.TELEPHONYEXCH.Definition: A telephony exchange is a device that ensures the routing of telephone calls and communications.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.TELEPHONYEXCH.Name: Telephony Exchange

UserCapacity.Name: User Capacity
UserCapacity.Definition: Indicates the user capacity of the device, defined as the maximum number of users that can be active at the same time.

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.TRANSITIONCOM.Definition: A transition component is a minor active device that converts electric signals to optical signals at the sender, and converts optical signals to electric signals at the receiver.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.TRANSITIONCOM.Name: Transition Component

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.TRANSPONDER.Definition: A transponder is a communication, monitoring, or control device that, upon receiving a signal, emits a different signal in response. Transponders can be either passive or active (e.g., electronic beacon, balise).
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.TRANSPONDER.Name: Transponder

DetectionRange.Name: Detection Range
DetectionRange.Definition: The detection range of the equipment.

InformationLength.Name: Information Length
InformationLength.Definition: Indicates supported bytes of the data Information, e.g.127 bytes.

IP_Code.Name: Ip_Code
IP_Code.Definition: IP Code, the International Protection Marking, IEC 60529), classifies and rates the degree of protection provided against intrusion.

NominalHeight.Name: Nominal Height
NominalHeight.Definition: The nominal height of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

NominalLength.Name: Nominal Length
NominalLength.Definition: The nominal overall length of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In case of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

NominalWidth.Name: Nominal Width
NominalWidth.Definition: The nominal overall width of the object. The size information is provided in addition to the shape representation and the geometric parameters used within. In cases of inconsistency between the geometric parameters and the size properties, provided in the attached property set, the geometric parameters take precedence.

OperationalTemperatureRange.Description: This property in IFC stores a bounded value, meaning it has a maximum of two (numeric or descriptive) values assigned, the first value specifying the upper bound and the second value specifying the lower bound. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
OperationalTemperatureRange.Name: Operational Temperature Range
OperationalTemperatureRange.Definition: The temperature range in which the device operates normally.

TransmissionRate.Name: Transmission Rate
TransmissionRate.Definition: Data transmission rate between the device and the receiving module in bits per second.

IfcCommunicationsAppliance.TRANSPORTEQUI.Definition: A transport equipment is a network element responsible for providing functionality of transport, multiplexing, switching, management and supervision of transmission channels between different hosts. The data transport service uses three specific metrics: the bandwidth, the jitter, and the packet loss rate.
IfcCommunicationsAppliance.TRANSPORTEQUI.Name: Transport Equipment

ElectricalCrossCapacity.Name: Electrical Cross Capacity
ElectricalCrossCapacity.Definition: Indicates the electrical cross capacity of the transport equipment.

IsUpgradable.Name: Is Upgradable
IsUpgradable.Definition: Indicates whether the transport equipment can be upgraded or not.

TransportEquipmentAssemblyType.Name: Transport Equipment Assembly Type
TransportEquipmentAssemblyType.Definition: Indicates the type of transport equipment assembly.

TransportEquipmentType.Name: Transport Equipment Type
TransportEquipmentType.Definition: Indicates the type of transport equipment.

ChromaticDispersionTolerance.Name: Chromatic Dispersion Tolerance
ChromaticDispersionTolerance.Definition: Indicates the tolerance of the transport equipment chromatic dispersion. The value is defined by picosecond per nanometer (ps/nm).

EquipmentCapacity.Name: Equipment Capacity
EquipmentCapacity.Definition: Indicates the equipment capacity of the appliance. The value is defined in bits/s.

MinimumOpticalSignalToNoiseRatio.Name: Minimum Optical Signal to Noise Ratio
MinimumOpticalSignalToNoiseRatio.Definition: Indicates the minimum optical signal to noise ratio of the transport equipment.

PolarizationModeDispersionTolerance.Name: Polarization Mode Dispersion Tolerance
PolarizationModeDispersionTolerance.Definition: Indicates the polarization mode dispersion tolerance of the transport equipment. It is usually measured by picosecond.

SingleChannelAveragePower.Name: Single Channel Average Power
SingleChannelAveragePower.Definition: Indicates the average power of a single channel of the transport equipment.

SingleChannelPower.Description: This property in IFC stores a bounded value, meaning it has a maximum of two (numeric or descriptive) values assigned, the first value specifying the upper bound and the second value specifying the lower bound. Read the IFC documentation for more information.
SingleChannelPower.Name: Single Channel Power
SingleChannelPower.Definition: Indicates the power range of a single channel of the transport equipment.

SingleWaveTransmissionRate.Name: Single Wave Transmission Rate
SingleWaveTransmissionRate.Definition: Indicates the single wave transmission rate of the transport equipment.

IfcDistributionBoard.CONSUMERUNIT.Definition: A distribution point on the incoming electrical supply, typically in domestic premises, at which protective devices are located.
IfcDistributionBoard.CONSUMERUNIT.Name: Consumer Unit

IfcDistributionBoard.DISPATCHINGBOARD.Definition: A distribution point at which voice and data communication signals are managed between communication devices.
IfcDistributionBoard.DISPATCHINGBOARD.Name: Dispatching Board

DispatchingBoardType.Name: Dispatching Board Type
DispatchingBoardType.Definition: Indicates the type of dispatching board.

NumberOfInterfaces.Definition: Indicates the types of interfaces and their number in the device.

IfcDistributionBoard.DISTRIBUTIONBOARD.Definition: A distribution point at which connections are made for distribution of electrical circuits usually through protective devices.
IfcDistributionBoard.DISTRIBUTIONBOARD.Name: Distribution Board

IfcDistributionBoard.DISTRIBUTIONFRAME.Definition: A distribution frame is used to interconnect and manage wiring between active equipment and subscriber. It might be composed of multiple distribution boards and other components.
IfcDistributionBoard.DISTRIBUTIONFRAME.Name: Distribution Frame

PortCapacity.Name: Port Capacity
PortCapacity.Definition: Indicates the number of ports in the passive device that can be used to interconnect cables.

IfcDistributionBoard.MOTORCONTROLCENTRE.Definition: A distribution point at which starting and control devices for major plant items are located.
IfcDistributionBoard.MOTORCONTROLCENTRE.Name: Motor Control Centre

IfcDistributionBoard.SWITCHBOARD.Definition: A distribution point at which switching devices are located.
IfcDistributionBoard.SWITCHBOARD.Name: Switch Board

IfcElectricAppliance.DISHWASHER.Definition: An appliance that has the primary function of washing dishes.
IfcElectricAppliance.DISHWASHER.Name: Dishwasher

IfcElectricAppliance.ELECTRICCOOKER.Definition: An electrical appliance that has the primary function of cooking food (including oven, hob, grill).
IfcElectricAppliance.ELECTRICCOOKER.Name: Electriccooker

IfcElectricAppliance.FREESTANDINGELECTRI.Definition: An electrical appliance that is used occasionally to provide heat. A freestanding electric heater is a 'plugged' appliance whose load may be removed from an electric circuit.
IfcElectricAppliance.FREESTANDINGELECTRI.Name: Freestandingelectricheater

IfcElectricAppliance.FREESTANDINGFAN.Definition: An electrical appliance that is used occasionally to provide ventilation. A freestanding fan is a 'plugged' appliance whose load may be removed from an electric circuit.
IfcElectricAppliance.FREESTANDINGFAN.Name: Freestanding Fan

IfcElectricAppliance.FREESTANDINGWATERCO.Definition: A small, local electrical appliance for cooling water. A freestanding water cooler is a 'plugged' appliance whose load may be removed from an electric circuit.
IfcElectricAppliance.FREESTANDINGWATERCO.Name: Freestanding Water Cooler

IfcElectricAppliance.FREESTANDINGWATERHE.Definition: A small, local electrical appliance for heating water. A freestanding water heater is a 'plugged' appliance whose load may be removed from an electric circuit.
IfcElectricAppliance.FREESTANDINGWATERHE.Name: Freestanding Water Heater

IfcElectricAppliance.FREEZER.Definition: An electrical appliance that has the primary function of storing food at temperatures below the freezing point of water.
IfcElectricAppliance.FREEZER.Name: Freezer

IfcElectricAppliance.FRIDGE_FREEZER.Definition: An electrical appliance that combines the functions of a freezer and a refrigerator through the provision of separate compartments.
IfcElectricAppliance.FRIDGE_FREEZER.Name: Fridge Freezer

IfcElectricAppliance.HANDDRYER.Definition: An electrical appliance that has the primary function of drying hands.
IfcElectricAppliance.HANDDRYER.Name: Hand Dryer

IfcElectricAppliance.KITCHENMACHINE.Definition: A specialized appliance used in commercial kitchens such as a mixer.
IfcElectricAppliance.KITCHENMACHINE.Name: Kitchen Machine

IfcElectricAppliance.MICROWAVE.Definition: An electrical appliance that has the primary function of cooking food using microwaves.
IfcElectricAppliance.MICROWAVE.Name: Microwave

IfcElectricAppliance.PHOTOCOPIER.Definition: A machine that has the primary function of reproduction of printed matter.
IfcElectricAppliance.PHOTOCOPIER.Name: Photocopier

IfcElectricAppliance.REFRIGERATOR.Definition: An electrical appliance that has the primary function of storing food at low temperature but above the freezing point of water.
IfcElectricAppliance.REFRIGERATOR.Name: Refrigerator

IfcElectricAppliance.TUMBLEDRYER.Definition: An electrical appliance that has the primary function of drying clothes.
IfcElectricAppliance.TUMBLEDRYER.Name: Tumble Dryer

IfcElectricAppliance.VENDINGMACHINE.Definition: An appliance that stores and vends goods including food, drink, tickets, and goods of various types.
IfcElectricAppliance.VENDINGMACHINE.Name: Vending Machine

MoneyStuckRatio.Name: Money Stuck Ratio
MoneyStuckRatio.Definition: Indicates the ratio of money being stuck or jammed in appliance.

PaymentMethod.Name: Payment Method
PaymentMethod.Definition: Indicates the vending machine payment method.

TicketProductionSpeed.Name: Ticket Production Speed
TicketProductionSpeed.Definition: Indicates the production speed of the ticket. It is measured by counting the number of tickets that can be produced per hour.

TicketStuckRatio.Name: Ticket Stuck Ratio
TicketStuckRatio.Definition: Indicates the ratio of tickets being stuck or jammed in the appliance.

TicketVendingMachineType.Name: Ticket Vending Machine Type
TicketVendingMachineType.Definition: Indicates the type of ticket vending machine.

VendingMachineUserInterface.Name: Vending Machine User Interface
VendingMachineUserInterface.Definition: Indicates the type of vending machine user interface.

IfcElectricAppliance.WASHINGMACHINE.Definition: An appliance that has the primary function of washing clothes.
IfcElectricAppliance.WASHINGMACHINE.Name: Washing Machine

IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.BATTERY.Definition: A device for storing energy in chemical form so that it can be released as electrical energy.
IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.BATTERY.Name: Battery

EncapsulationTechnologyCode.Definition: Code indicating the encapsulation technology which has been applied in an electric, electronic or electromechanical component.

NominalSupplyCurrent.Definition: The nominal current of the supply.

OpenCircuitVoltage.Definition: Voltage of a cell or battery when the discharge current is zero [Source IEC 482-03-32]

VoltageRegulationRate.Name: Voltage Regulation Rate
VoltageRegulationRate.Definition: When the input side voltage changes from the lowest allowable input value to the specified maximum value, the relative change value of the output voltage is the percentage of the rated output voltage.

IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.CAPACITOR.Definition: A device that stores electric charge when an external power supply is present using the electrical property of capacitance. Two-terminal device characterized essentially by its capacitance.; Note: definition from IEC 60050 151-13-28.
IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.CAPACITOR.Name: Capacitor

NumberOfPhases.Name: Number of Phases
NumberOfPhases.Definition: Number of phases that the equipment operates on.

IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.CAPACITORBA.Definition: A device that stores electrical energy when an external power supply is present using the electrical property of capacitance.
IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.CAPACITORBA.Name: Capacitorbank

IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.COMPENSATOR.Definition: A device that is used to fix or adjust the parameter of electric energy, such as voltage loss, power factor and so on.
IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.COMPENSATOR.Name: Compensator

IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.HARMONICFIL.Definition: A device that constantly injects currents that precisely correspond to the harmonic components drawn by the load.
IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.HARMONICFIL.Name: Harmonic Filter

IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.INDUCTOR.Definition: A device used in circuits or power systems due to their inductance, acting as a component of electric storage device.
IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.INDUCTOR.Name: Inductor

NumberOfPhases.Name: Number of Phases
NumberOfPhases.Definition: Number of phases that the equipment operates on.

IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.INDUCTORBAN.Definition: A device that stores electrical energy in a magnetic field using electrical property of inductance.
IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.INDUCTORBAN.Name: Inductorbank

IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.RECHARGER.Definition: A recharger or battery charger is a device used to put energy into a secondary cell or rechargeable battery by forcing an electric current through it.
IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.RECHARGER.Name: Recharger

NominalSupplyCurrent.Name: Nominal Supply Current
NominalSupplyCurrent.Definition: The nominal current of the supply.

IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.UPS.Definition: A device that provides a time limited alternative source of power supply in the event of failure of the main supply.
IfcElectricFlowStorageDevice.UPS.Name: UPS
